National Highways reported just after 4pm that the incident had forced one lane to close heading southbound between Junction 17 and Junction 16, in Cheshire. It said that there were already 6 miles of congestion on the approach.  It estimated at least 40 minutes of delays for drivers using the stretch of motorway. The roads agency said that the accident had been cleared, but that severe congestion remained. As of 4.25pm, all lanes had been reopened. However, National Highways said that around 44 minutes of delays and over 7 miles of congestion remained. Junction 16 is the Barthomley interchange with the A500, near Crewe. Junction 17 is the Sandbach interchange with the A534. As of 5pm, the incident had cleared. 